    public abstract class InputField<T>
extends Field<T>
    Base class for input field. Example of input field are text input and LOV field

    • Field Detail

      • alter

        protected java.lang.String alter
        Case for the value. Valid value are U (Upper), 0(Lower) and N(Normal)

      • value

        protected java.lang.String value
        Value for the input field.

      • required

        protected boolean required
        required flag. If it is required, then the field have to has a value before it can move to other field

      • length

        protected int length
        set value length

      • valueType

        protected int valueType
        set value type

      • dateTimeFormat

        protected java.lang.String dateTimeFormat
        set date format if the value type is date and set time format if the value type is time;

      • readOnly

        protected boolean readOnly
        readOnly flag. If it is readOnly, the value can changed.

      • type

        protected java.lang.String type
        type of input field. Sample textarea, textinput, date.

      • barcodeDelimiter

        protected java.lang.String barcodeDelimiter
        BarcodeType delimiter. This value will be used to cut the barcode, retrieve the value and pass the rest to the next field

      • DFI

        protected java.lang.String DFI
        BenchmarkData Field Identifier. This value is used to identify the value from barcode.

      • DFIRequired

        protected boolean DFIRequired
        BenchmarkData Field Identifier required flag. If it is true, then when scan by barcode, the prefix have to match the DFI value.

      • defaultValue

        protected java.lang.String defaultValue
        Default value logic. This can either a script, a sql, name of the object in session or just a constant value

      • onKeyEnter

        protected java.lang.String onKeyEnter
        On Key Enter event. This value is a script that will be executed when user hit an "enter" key

      • enableGenerate

        protected boolean enableGenerate
        This variable is used to determine whether the generate icon should be shown when the cursor is on this component. Generate icon is used to do Ctrl-G

      • doAction

        public void doAction(com.intellinum.mia.app.action.Action action)
              throws java.lang.Exception
        Description copied from class: FlexiUIObject
        Action taken when receive an input from server. when create a new UI class, override this function as needed For Example, when creating a new button UI class, it needs a special handle when the button is pressed. So the new class should override this function, using if commands to capture the SUBMIT action and then do the desired behaviour. if the commands is not SUBMIT, the pass it to the super.doAction;
